description.narrative:
Capacity Building Component: 
All the projects under this component have been terminated and reports submitted and approved except The Risk assessment in relation to Safety and Occupational Health and Environment and Introduction of LMS and E-Learning at EDM which are on-going.
The final report of the risk assessment has been submitted and is under review.
For the e-learning project, the recording studio has been furnished and equipped and EDM staff is in training however the responsibility of managing the studio and the LMS has not been decided yet.
The major results of the CBP are:
a) Commercial work processes have been reviewed which have served as an input to the Integrated Management System SIGEM;
b) International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) have been introduced and EDM is now reporting in accordance with these standards;
c) The Meter Policy has been updated;
d) An “Automated Meter Reading System (MV90) Maintenance Manual” has been formulated and training performed;
e) Procurement of metering quality equipment and training to use this equipment has been performed;
f) A draft Loss Reduction Plan has been formulated;
g) A Losses Database has been constructed and six single user software licenses have been purchased;
h) An Energy Efficiency (EE) strategy;
i) an EE Awareness strategy;
j) Demand Market Participation (DMP) strategy;
k) and a Demand Side Management (DSM) strategy have been formulated, as well as a ToR for Energy Efficiency (EE) implementation support;
Norway is financing a support programme for implementation of the Procurement Reform Plan with the objective to implement best practices, and reverse the trend of corruption and non-ethical activities in the supply chain. 
 Strategic Studies Component:
Three feasibility studies have been perfomed and approved by the EoS, that is:
- Massinga-Vilanculos Transmission Line
- Tsate Hydropower Plant
- Rehabilitation of Corumana Hydropower Plant
As a result of the above studies follow up studies of Massinga - Vilanculos transmission Line ESIA (Environmental and Social Impact Assessment) and the Tsate Line route ESIA are being conducted under the Project Preparation Facility agreement (PPF) with EDM.
Five Project Identification Studies also have been completed and approved by th EoS:
- Mavuzi II Hydropower Plant
- Lucite Hydropower Plant
- Mutelele Hydropower Plant
- Expansion of Temane Gas
-UGDE (EDM Performance Management)
Two additional studies have been completed and are awaiting approval:
- Nampula-Angoche Transmission Line ESIA
-Electrification of Administrative Posts Feasibility Study
